---

## Mandatory Rules

### MUST

- Keep business rules outside AI.
- Version every prompt.
- Validate every AI response.
- Use structured outputs for business workflows.
- Monitor token usage and AI costs.
- Protect against prompt injection.
- Enforce tenant isolation.
- Maintain complete audit trails.
- Search the repository before creating AI artifacts.
- Test every AI capability before deployment.

### MUST NOT

- Allow AI to modify business state directly.
- Hardcode prompts in Java classes.
- Depend on a single LLM provider.
- Execute tools without authorization.
- Retrieve knowledge across tenants.
- Trust unvalidated AI output.
- Ignore hallucinations.
- Deploy AI without monitoring.
- Duplicate prompts, agents, or retrievers.
- Bypass Business Services or Workflow Engine.

---

